Review: Huggies wipes have quickly become a must-have in our household! They’re soft and gentle, which is perfect for my baby's sensitive skin, but they’re also durable enough to handle any mess. The thickness is just right—not too thin, so they don’t tear, but also not too thick, making them easy to maneuver for quick clean-ups.The wipes are also very moist without being overly wet, so they leave my baby’s skin feeling fresh but not sticky. They’re fragrance-free, which I appreciate since it reduces the risk of irritation. I love that the packaging is designed for easy access, with a pop-up lid that keeps them moist and ready to use.Overall, Huggies wipes are effective, gentle, and convenient—a true essential!

My husband and I tried both Huggies and Pampers brand wipes when our daughter was born and these are hands down the best of the two. These wipes are super absorbent, are nice a wet but not too wet that I feel like I have to wring them out. They have soft texture so they clean well instead of smearing. They are durable and much better price wise compared to Pampers.The biggest selling point was the fact that when you only want one wipe, it’s so easy to just get one. With Pampers wipes, they stick to each other in the package so you go to pull one out and you get five. If you only want one, you have to use two hands. With Huggies wipes you just get one every time. They are loosely attached and separate easily when pulled out. The next wipe is easy to grab and again, you only get one each time. The Disney geek in me also loves the Winnie the Pooh packaging.The only downside is that Huggies doesn’t have a rewards program right now so I can’t get any rewards points on wipes like I can with Pampers.

They are unscented, thick and big enough to use a single wipe at a time. It is strong enough to withstand normal use and does not tear. Soft to the touch and is wet enough. It will meet all your expectations from a baby wipe.
One wipe goes a long way, love these baby wipes, and my baby doesn’t break out, they are affordable and gets the job done

I recently purchased a pack of Huggies diapers for my little one, and I am thrilled with the quality and performance of these diapers. Huggies has always been a trusted brand when it comes to baby care, and these diapers have certainly lived up to their reputation.First and foremost, the fit of these diapers is excellent. They are designed with a snug and comfortable fit that keeps my baby dry and secure. The elastic waistband and stretchy sides ensure a proper fit without any leaks or discomfort. I appreciate how these diapers adapt to my baby's movements, providing a secure and flexible fit throughout the day.The absorbency of Huggies diapers is outstanding. They are equipped with a highly effective absorbent core that quickly locks away wetness, keeping my baby's skin dry and rash-free. Even during overnight use, these diapers have proven to be reliable in preventing leaks and maintaining dryness. This gives me peace of mind knowing that my baby is comfortable and protected.I also appreciate the breathability of these diapers. The materials used are soft and breathable, allowing for proper airflow and preventing any irritation or diaper rash. This is especially important for my baby's sensitive skin, and Huggies diapers have proven to be gentle and non-irritating.The design of these diapers is also adorable. The fun and colorful prints add a touch of cuteness to my baby's outfit. It's a small detail, but it definitely adds to the overall positive experience of using these diapers.Furthermore, the packaging of Huggies diapers is convenient and user-friendly. The resealable tabs make it easy to open and close, ensuring that the diapers stay fresh and organized. The clear size indicators on the packaging also make it simple to find the right size for my growing baby.Lastly, I appreciate the availability and affordability of Huggies diapers. They are readily available in most stores and online, making it convenient for me to purchase them whenever needed. Considering the quality and performance they offer, I find these diapers to be reasonably priced and a great value for money.In conclusion, I highly recommend Huggies diapers to any parent or caregiver. Their excellent fit, superb absorbency, breathability, and adorable design make them a top choice for keeping your baby dry, comfortable, and happy. With their convenient packaging and affordability, Huggies diapers have become a staple in my baby care routine, and I am extremely satisfied with my purchase.

I'VE BEEN USING THIS PARTICULAR HUGGIES WIPES FOR SEVERAL YEARS. I used to use a different brand of wipes. But after a couple of years of buying them, the manufacturer went cheap and changed the material to such an inferrior cloth, that the material would fall apart and leave a bunch of loose cotton all over your skin. NOT GOOD. Becuase now you have to actually wash it off. That's when I switched to Huggies, and have been using them for at least five (5) years.MANY USAGES:I take these wipes with me everywhere, because you never know when you'll need them. And particularly in the Summer, when it's hot and muggy out; I use them to clean and cool off my face, arms and legs, etc... And no matter where I am, when I'm away from home, I always run into moms who needs one for her child. These wipes  come in handy for cleaning faces and hands after a meal, while on the run or at home.TEXTURE:These wipes are sturdy and easy to manage with one hand. Their more than just wipes, their like wash cloths. They don't fall apart, their super soft, and have enough moisture in them to clean your parts effectively. The package says their hypoallergenic, and I believe it, because my family have been using this brand for many years, and no one has broken out from them. We love them, especially for the bathroom.LIKE WASHING WITH WATER:Another good use is using the wipes like your're washing your hands with water.  I carry a wad of these wipes with me when on the go, so when I'm away from home and really need to give my hands a wash, I just squeeze the soapy water out the wipe into my hand and rub both hands together, as if to be washing my hands with soap and water. Then I use the wipe to finish the job. Works every time.EASY TO OPEN FLIP-TOP:I like this brand of Huggies for many reasons, and the easy flip top was one of the main reasons I keep coming back. You can actually flip the top open and closed with one hand, which I do frequently. So, that's a feature that comes in handy when I don't have both hands available.PRICE IS COST EFFECTIVE:As you know, wipes can be very expenseive; $4, $5 or more just for one pack, and not get many wipes either. Many times the local store runs out of the brand you like, and you're stuck paying a lot of money for a small pack and a brand you're not familiar with. This particular item of Huggies, sold on Amazon comes in a  bundle of 11 flip-top packs, so you'll have plenty on hand for a long time. AND THE PRICE IS GREAT, TOO; I bought this item in October 2023, and paid less than $19 dollars, including taxes. With 11 packs in the bundle, that makes the average price for one pack less than $2 bucks!RECOMMEND?: Absolutely! I recommend this item to anyone who wants a wipe thats super soft, hypoallergenic, has lots of soap and water and cleans like a wash cloth. Oh, the size is great too!

Great durability for price. Got a good deal when these were bought. Functional and seals well. Unscented. Pulls the wetness away from babies bottom which keeps them a little cleaner and helps protect the skin.

Been buying these for years! After trying many brands and types of wipes, these are the clear winner! Best quality and durability and fair price. No smell. No sticky residue. Great for baby diapers but for many other uses too.The only annoying part is how sometimes it’s hard to pull out just one, and a whole bunch come outAlso the part that you’re supposed to rip open could be made a bit better

Top-Notch Quality and Gentle CareHuggies Baby Wipes are an absolute must-have for parents seeking reliable, high-quality wipes that are gentle on delicate skin. These wipes are thick, soft, and have just the right amount of moisture, making clean-up easy and efficient without having to use a ton of wipes. They’re durable enough to handle even the toughest messes without tearing, which makes diaper changes quicker and less messy.The formula is gentle and hypoallergenic, free from harsh chemicals, so it’s safe for sensitive skin and leaves babies feeling fresh without irritation. Huggies also offers different varieties like fragrance-free and aloe-infused options to suit specific needs, which is a thoughtful touch.Overall, Huggies Baby Wipes combine durability, softness, and skin-safe ingredients, making them a fantastic choice for parents who want only the best for their babies. Highly recommended!

I first heard of these boxes from YouTube reviews and saw that the boxes were filled with lots of deluxe size samples as well as full size products. This no-touch thermometer has been an absolute game-changer!What I love: * Speed:  It delivers a temperature reading literally in one second. No more waiting and wondering, especially with a fussy child. * Accuracy: I've compared the readings to my old oral thermometer, and they're consistently spot on. * Ease of Use:  Simply point, click, and read. This is a very durable, easy to use and accurate thermometer. It’s push button simple. I recommend this digital thermometer.

Very lightweight and simple to use. It works much quicker than our other thermometers and it’s very easy to read. Great value for the price. I recommended it to several of my friends who were also happy with the purchase.  It often off by a degree but I have gotten use to that.

I have had tinnitus since I was young.  The ringing is too loud when I am trying to go to sleep at night where it is quiet.  I would try a radio or a fan.  I had a clock radio that had sounds and when it stopped working I was back to having a hard time getting to sleep.  This device is small and it works for me.  It does not bother the wife so it is a win win.  With all the different sound to choose from you can find the right one for you.  Various volume helps a lot.  Another nice thing is you can take it with you on trips.  So get one.

I’ve been using this product for about a year now in my home office. I was desperate to drown out the incessant barking from a next door neighbor’s dog so I could concentrate on work. I’m also on the phone a lot and didn’t want the dog to be heard in the background. We did try talking to our neighbor about the dog, which had minimal effect. Since using this device, my stress level has gone way down and I am much less distracted. This tiny little machine packs a big punch! It can get REALLY loud, but I’ve figured out the ideal volume for me (about halfway up) and that, combined with my bluetooth ear piece which reduces background noise, ensures I can have professional phone calls again and no one has ever mentioned they can’t hear me. The device also helps when my son is home from school on a break and won’t stop yelling at his video game in the basement (haha). At first, I felt resentful that due to my inconsiderate neighbor, I had to purchase this device, but now I’ve gotten so used to it I barely think about it anymore. It’s the first thing I turn on after hitting the light switch when I go into my office each morning. In fact, I love it so much I just purchased a second one for my husband to use in the basement, when the dog starts going off. It’s so affordable, I may eventually end up getting one for every room in the house. It also blocks out loud construction noises and other annoying environmental sounds. It does begin to auto-shut off after about 2 hrs (not sure if that’s a built in feature or if I could somehow bypass it), but once I notice the sound decreasing, I just hit the power button and it’s another 2 hrs of being in my peaceful cocoon.

We got this for white noise for our babies nursery and it works perfectly. We even bring it with us when we travel because it's so small and easy to pack. For the size the sound quality is really good, and there are so many sound options. Controls are easy to use, and the timer function works well, but we don't use it often.

The 20 sounds, some of them are useless or duplicates.  I played with the device a few times when I first got it to get the hang of it.- You can keep the device on indefinitely if you want- Press the button to cycle through the 20 sounds- Timer up to 5 hours which is pretty good- If you can't seem to get the device to go back to the sound #1 (default white noise sound), then you can hold the power button and plug the device back in and it will reset back to the beginning.- Sound volume and quality are good, not sold on the "non repeating" feature as advertised, but may be true- Small footprint is good for home or travel- Warranty??

One of the best items I've ever spent money on. I was having trouble sleeping at one point, and for a while would turn the fan on in my bathroom and let it run all night, to provide white noise, and also to block out the repetitive sounds my senior dog makes lol. (For context, she is very old and had some teeth pulled, so she smacks her mouth and lips a lot. She also can get anxious sometimes and likes to lick her bed, apparently it helps soothe her. None of that is her fought and I don't hold it against her, but as you can imagine, the sounds are not the greatest thing to hear when trying to fall asleep haha.) Anyways, I'm a very worrisome person and I began to get paranoid that leaving my bathroom fan on all night could be a potential fire hazard. So I stopped using it and began looking into noise machines. I looked at so many different kinds and eventually settled on this one. It ended up being perfect and is everything I wanted, plus more.Some cool features: You can change the timer for how long it stays on, or set it to just run all night, which is my go to setting. If you do set a timer, the white noise it creates doesn't just stop suddenly, it slowly fades out so not to disturb your sleep, which I think is a really cool part of its design. The volume buttons are easy to locate and do exactly what they're supposed to do. It also has a plethora of different sounds to use. My most favorite is the sound of heavy rain fall. I also use the bathroom fan sound quite a lot as well. Another feature I like is that it doesn't have a ton of bright lights on it. If you choose to turn the timer on, it will show a very faint dot based on which timer you pick. Because I let it run all night, there aren't any faint dots that show up. It's also very travel friendly, very similar to tossing a phone in your bag with its charger and walking out the door. I'll most likely buy a second one in the upcoming months for when I travel, that way my other one can stay at home. As far as sound quality goes, I give this noise machine a 10/10. The noises aren't scratchy or grating, but very natural and soothing. I've not had any issues with the volume or adjusting it and the speaker sounds great too.This little box has been a game changer for me in terms of falling asleep more easily, and I'm really glad I purchased it. If you're worried about it being complicated to use, don't be. It's super easy to setup, and basically plug and play. I've said it already, but I'm really happy with this purchase and it's definitely one of the best items I've spent money on. It's a quality item at a reasonable price and I couldn't be happier with it.Please Note: I was not paid to write this review. I was not given free merchandise to write this review. I wrote this review solely because I enjoyed this product and am very happy with my purchase.

My son loves everything with buttons to press and knobs to pull. I purchased this thinking that he would love the wheel too. He definitely does and what surprised me is the amount of ways he can interact with the toy, there are many buttons, a variety of cause and effect play options. It’s fun to watch him discover something new every time. He’s already dropped it a few times and it’s held up just fine- seems to be very durable. The size and weight is manageable for him. We keep it on the floor and it’s stable there unless he picks it up. The colors are fun and the noises are perfect for kid age + there are options for him as he grows. Overall stable, fun and a great toy for any curious baby. I would recommend this for a baby who can sit safely alone and has the hand eye coordination to play with it. I have a feeling he’ll be using this for years to come.

This toy is just the right size for our 10 month old boy to hold and chew. He is teething and the different textures are great for his gums. The multiple colors keep him interested. Well worth the money!
